## BUTTON VISIBILITY ALGORITHM

Buttons appear AFTER section content animates in. Prevents clicking next before seeing current content.

| Section | Appears When | Delay | Animation | 0 Ganesha | After all 4 shlok lines fade in | ~3.5s from page load | Fade in + scale 0.95->1.0 (0.4s) |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 Opening | After couple names + greeting animate | ~1.5s from section enter | Fade in + slide up 10px (0.4s) | 2 Events | Immediately -- always visible | 0s (fixed at bottom) | Fades in with section transition |
| 3 Gallery | After first gallery image loads | ~0.5s | Fade in + slide up 10px (0.4s) | 4 Countdown | After countdown + heading visible | ~0.8s | Fade in + slide up 10px (0.4s) |
| 5 RSVP | After invitation text visible | ~0.6s | Fade in + scale 0.95->1.0 + shimmer (0.5s) |  |  |  |  |

### Visibility Rules

- Buttons start `opacity: 0` + `pointer-events: none`
- When triggered: transition to `opacity: 1` + `pointer-events: auto`
- Once visible, buttons STAY visible for rest of section visit
- On revisit via nav: buttons appear immediately (no re-delay)
- Track with IntersectionObserver or section state
- NEVER hide a button after it appeared

